content: Hello, I bought new version a week or two ago. I imported all the previous data from old version and after that, I realized that this new version doesn't save model's pictures and I have to upload it every single time. This is very time consuming. I already deleted old version.. Please send me old version .apk. I will use it until you fix this problem in new version.
replyContent: This was deliberate because the feature was intended to add legal weight to the release by providing an image that places the model in the context of the shoot, not just a likeness of them. All your previous purchases can be found in your purchase history: Play Store app --> Menu --> My Apps and Games --> Library

replyContent: Please share specific issues with our support about which features you find difficult, so they may help you with them.

content: Forced to upgrade to new version to import data from older version of the app. Ok, another $9.99 , not the end of the world. Why did the old version keep all the photos with the model data but this version makes me take a new photo every time? Still a good app and I do recommend it to other photographers.
replyContent: There's no forced upgrade. Old version can use Android Auto Backup with GDrive to backup and restore in both old and new versions. Happy to refund you if you purchased the new version with this misunderstanding and want to go back to the old version. The photo feature is meant to add weight to the release by placing the model at the shoot.

content: Cannot select the "Adult" option of DOB, it forces me to type in a DOB instead. This has been resolved by the response below. The design is a bit unclear and can be improved.
replyContent: There is a setting that enables/disables the "Adult" & "Minor" buttons as many stock photo agencies require an actual DOB and the buttons often caused confusion and deleted birthdates.

content: Easy to set up. Easy to handle. Easy to work with models.

Good app. Does what it's supposed to (I think). However, $10 for an app that produces release forms with just 2 standard agreements is very overpriced imho. Then on top of that I have to pay another $7 for actual "Pro" features. How do you justify that? Why is it called Easy Release PRO if professional features have to be bought separately? Seems greedy. Would give it 5 stars if I didn't have to pay for professional customization. Also, the UI could maybe use an update but that's minor.

App is fairly simple to navigate and support has been very responsive to all of my questions and issues. I am not currently adding ID photos or sending releases to 3rd parties so this works for my purposes. At least now I don't have to print a bunch of stuff in advance.
This app is super helpful
Lifesaver :)
Very easy to use. My clients love it
Everything we need as filmmakers for our shoots in one single app. You can add this to any stock site and have all rights clared.

I use it for stock photography. it is a good app but one function is really missing: the ability to choose the date format. Most agencies only take releases dates as DD-MM-YYYY and ideally it would have to be dates with the month spelled out to avoid missinerpretation so like: 01 August 2019. Is this something that you could offer? I would pay for that feature
replyContent: We support date formats d/m/y for all languages except USA-English, which is m/d/y.  You simply have to switch to English-NON USA, or any other language. We also indicate right next to the date what the format is like this: d/m/y or m/d/y. This was all done in conjunction with the leading stock photo agencies who ALL accept Easy Release.

content: Great app, super easy to use, if you're having doubts about it, don't, just download!

I bought this apps. I found shutterstock did not accept MR from this application. Any reason? Or do you have suggestions if I can buy any other than this apps?
replyContent: Easy Release is the ONLY app approved by Shutterstock for model/property releases. If they reject a release it is always an error they're found on the release. We can't prevent user error but contacting our support may help you resolve the issue.

content: Some times Shatterstock doesn't support release from this app
replyContent: Thanks!  Shutterstock absolutely accept our releases but the require our default built-in release be used at all times. Contact us for details if you need them.

Good app for model releases
Bought the app and upgrade to pro, and purchased advance customization and again purchased multi page release, but i cant see any difference. What happening i spent money for nothing?????
replyContent: The built-in releases are not editable so that they remain compliant with stock photo industry standards, but you can create as many custom release templates as you want and apply all the customization options to these.

content: I was very happy with the old standard version. Now I upgraded my tablet and wanted to install it in my new one. BUT IT IS GONE!!. And I need it to buy it again???? I had no option as I was going to a shoot. But I think it is unfair. I understand this is a NEW? version (I could not find any substantial change) You may said you can add other options, but those options are not really important for most of us. I even bought the extension (silly me) to try to find something really new. As I mentioned before, nothing really substantial. If you want to offer a "BETTER??? PRO VERSION" it is ok by me. But you should keep the "STANDARD" available and let the old users to choose if the want to upgrade or not. On top of this, the "NEW - PRO- MORE COMPLICATED VERSION" do not have a proper user manual. The "on-line" help or the FAQ (instructions about how to set up the app are in the FAQ area - unbelieve) are far to be enough and I still cannot use the "IMPROVEMENTS" as I have no idea how to use or what for are the "New options". So far I used to recommend this app to all my colleagues. now I am very disappointed. At least make a proper PDF downloadable full manual please explaining all the new options, with examples. One more thing: do not take the easy way and offer a refund. Just make the things properly.
replyContent: The "original version" of the app is always available in your Play Store App's purchase history for free. Not our fault that you don't know this and that Google also failed to make an app easy enough. Help documentation is spread throughout the app under the Menu, inline with the features.

content: Great tool for anyone that does anything photographic. Easy to use once you tour around a bit. Definitely my go-to app for my business
